The paper discusses profiling and characterization of machine learning models, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on optimizing system performance for ML models, which involves hardware and system design, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically mentions GPUs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Additionally, the paper proposes a profiling design that can be applied across different levels of the hardware/software stack, which could be relevant to architecture (cs.AR) research.
